modules.description: Processes OpenStreetMap XML data by parsing and extracting node, way, and relation elements. Handles tag and attribute extraction using custom parsing logic and recursive traversal. Used to transform raw OSM XML into structured in-memory representations for geographic data analysis.

Provides basic type definitions for OSM object representations. Includes core data types such as identifiers, coordinates, and metadata structures. Supports operations for constructing and inspecting these types in spatial data processing. Enables precise handling of node, way, and relation structures within mapping applications.

Parses XML input to extract OSM data structures, including nodes, ways, relations, and tags, using attribute lookup and tree traversal. Works with XML attributes, trees, and custom OSM types like osm_node, osm_way, and osm_relation. Processes OSM XML files to construct a complete OSM data model with configurable parsing options.
